#
# Journal message catalog for MurphyOS
# Install: journalctl --update-catalog < murphy.catalog
#
# Each entry is referenced by a 128-bit message ID and provides contextual
# help shown by `journalctl --catalog`.

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20001
Subject: Murphy confidence score changed
Defined-By: murphy-system

The Murphy Fractal Governance Confidence (MFGC) score has changed.

A rising score indicates healthy system operation; a falling score may
indicate anomalies or degraded inputs.  Gate policies use this value to
decide whether autonomous actions are allowed.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=confidence, MURPHY_CONFIDENCE, MURPHY_CONFIDENCE_OLD

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/governance/confidence

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20002
Subject: Murphy governance gate decision
Defined-By: murphy-system

A governance gate evaluated the current confidence score and rendered an
allow, deny, or escalate decision.

When a gate denies an action the system pauses autonomous execution and
waits for human approval.  Escalation routes the decision to the HITL
dashboard.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=gate, MURPHY_GATE_NAME, MURPHY_GATE_ACTION, MURPHY_CONFIDENCE

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/governance/gates

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20003
Subject: Murphy swarm agent lifecycle event
Defined-By: murphy-system

A swarm agent was spawned, terminated, or encountered an error.

Every agent is identified by a UUID stored in MURPHY_AGENT_ID.
Resources allocated to the agent are tracked in the murphy.slice cgroup
hierarchy.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=swarm, MURPHY_AGENT_ID, MURPHY_SWARM_ACTION, MURPHY_SWARM_ROLE

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/swarm/lifecycle

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20004
Subject: Murphy security engine event
Defined-By: murphy-system

One of the MurphyOS security engines (auto-encrypt, auto-patch, network
sentinel, memory protection, etc.) reported a notable event.

Review the MURPHY_SECURITY_ENGINE field to identify the originating engine
and check the severity to determine urgency.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=security, MURPHY_SECURITY_ENGINE, MURPHY_SEVERITY

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/security

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20005
Subject: Murphy LLM inference request
Defined-By: murphy-system

An LLM inference request was completed.  Token counts and latency are
recorded for cost tracking and performance monitoring.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=llm, MURPHY_LLM_PROVIDER, MURPHY_LLM_MODEL,
        MURPHY_LLM_TOKENS, MURPHY_LLM_LATENCY_MS

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/llm/tracking

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20006
Subject: Murphy forge event
Defined-By: murphy-system

A code-forge or build event was recorded by the Murphy system.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=forge

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/forge

-- a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b20007
Subject: Murphy automation event
Defined-By: murphy-system

An automation workflow step was logged.  Automation events track task
execution, retries, and completion across the Murphy pipeline.

Fields: MURPHY_EVENT_TYPE=automation

Documentation: https://docs.murphy.ai/automation
